This code uses the equations in in Fong et al., "Onsager transport coefficients and transference numbers in polyelectrolyte solutions and polymerized ionic liquids" (https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.macromol.0c02001) to compute transport coefficients $L^{ij}$ in electrolyte solutions using the equation

$L^{ij} = \frac{1}{6k_{\mathrm{B}}TV}\lim_{t\to\infty}\frac{d}{dt} \big< \sum_{\alpha}[\boldsymbol{r}_i^{\alpha}(t)-\boldsymbol{r}_i^{\alpha}(0)]\cdot \sum_{\beta}[\boldsymbol{r}_j^{\beta}(t)-\boldsymbol{r}_j^{\beta}(0)]\big>$,

where $k_\mathrm{B}T$ is the thermal energy and $\boldsymbol{r}_i^{\alpha}$ is the position of particle $\alpha$ of type $i$ relative to the center of mass position of the system. We also compute the self and distinct components of the diagonal transport coefficients $L^{ii}$. The former is computed via

$L^{ii}_{\mathrm{self}} = \frac{1}{6k_{\mathrm{B}}TV}\lim_{t\to\infty}\frac{d}{dt} \sum_{\alpha}\big< [\boldsymbol{r}_i^{\alpha}(t)-\boldsymbol{r}_i^{\alpha}(0)]^2\big>$,

and the latter can be computed by $L^{ii}_{\mathrm{distinct}} = L^{ii} - L^{ii}_{\mathrm{self}}$. The self terms are related to the self-diffusion coefficients $D_i$ via $L^{ii}_{\mathrm{self}} = \frac{D_i c_i}{k_{\mathrm{B}}T}$. Throughout this example code we refer to the terms in angular brackets in the $L^{ij}$ and $L^{ii}_{\mathrm{self}}$ self equations as the "MSD", although it is only technically a mean-squared displacment in the latter case.

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def getAutoCorrelation(x):
    """
    Function to calculate the autocorrelation function using the fast Fourier transform.

    -----------------------------
    Parameters
    -----------------------------
    x : float array storing the values of the function at discrete intervals to compute the autocorrelation function

    -----------------------------
    Returns
    -----------------------------
    acf: float array returning the autocorrelation function
    """
    N = x.shape[0]    
    F = np.square(np.absolute(np.fft.fft(x, n = 2*N)))
    return (np.absolute(np.fft.ifft(F)[:N]) / (N * np.ones(N) - np.arange(0, N)))

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def getCrossCorrelation(x, y):
    """
    Function to calculate the cross-correlation function of x and y using the fast Fourier transform.

    ------------------------------
    Parameters
    ------------------------------
    x : float array storing the values of a function at discrete intervals to compute the autocorrelation function
    y : float array storing the values of another function at discrete intervals to compute the autocorrelation function

    ------------------------------
    Returns
    ------------------------------
    cf: float array returning the cross-correlation function
    """
    N = x.shape[0]
    F = np.multiply(np.fft.fft(x, n = 2*N), np.conjugate(np.fft.fft(y, n = 2*N)))
    return (np.real(np.fft.ifft(F)[:N]) / (N * np.ones(N) - np.arange(0, N)))

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def getMSD(ion_pos):
    """
    Function to compute the mean square displacement using the fast Fourier transform.

    ----------------------
    Inputs
    ----------------------
    ion_pos: float array storing the coordinates of the ion as it varies with time

    ----------------------
    Returns
    ----------------------
    msd: float array storing the mean-squared displacement over time
    """
    N = ion_pos.shape[0]
    D = np.append(np.sum(np.square(ion_pos), axis=1), 0)
    sum_2 = np.zeros(N)
    for i in range(ion_pos.shape[1]):
        sum_2 += getAutoCorrelation(ion_pos[:, i])
    Q = 2 * np.sum(D)
    sum = np.zeros(N)
    for i in range(N):
        Q -= (D[i - 1] + D[N - i])
        sum[i] = Q / (N - i)
    return (sum - 2 * sum_2)

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def getMSDcross(ion_pos1, ion_pos2):
    """
    Function to calculate the 'MSD' (cross-correlations) using the fast Fourier transform.

    ------------------
    Parameters
    ------------------
    ion_pos1  : float array storing the coordinates of ion of type 1 as it varies over time
    ion_pos2  : float array storing the coordinates of ion of type 2 as it varies over time

    ------------------
    Returns
    ------------------
    msd: float array storing the cross-correlated "MSD" over time
    """
    N = ion_pos1.shape[0]
    D = np.append(np.sum(np.multiply(ion_pos1, ion_pos2), axis = 1), 0) 
    sum_2 = np.zeros(N)
    sum_3 = np.zeros(N)
    for i in range(ion_pos1.shape[1]):
        sum_2 += getCrossCorrelation(ion_pos1[:, i], ion_pos2[:, i])
        sum_3 += getCrossCorrelation(ion_pos2[:, i], ion_pos1[:, i])
    Q = 2 * np.sum(D)
    sum = np.zeros(N)
    for i in range(N):
        Q -= (D[i - 1] + D[N - i])
        sum[i] = Q / (N - i)
    
    return (sum - sum_2 - sum_3)

def getPositions(u, anions, cations, timeSteps):
    """
    Creates an array containing the positions of all cations and anions over time.

    -------------------------
    Inputs:
    -------------------------
    u         : an MDAnalysis universe
    anions    : an MDAnalysis AtomGroup containing the centre of mass of the anions
    cations   : an MDAnalysis AtomGroup containing the centre of mass of the cations
    timeSteps : int, number of time steps at which the position of the atoms was recorded

    -------------------------
    Returns:
    -------------------------
    anion_positions  : float array with all anion centre of geometry positions.
    cation_positions : float array with all cation centre of geometry positions.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively
    """
    time = 0
    anions = u.select_atoms('resname NTf2 and name N5')
    cations = u.select_atoms('resname LIG and name N01')
    anion_positions = np.zeros((timeSteps, len(anions), 3), dtype = np.float32)
    cation_positions = np.zeros((timeSteps, len(cations), 3), dtype = np.float32)
    COM = u.atoms.center_of_mass(wrap = True)
    for ts in u.trajectory:
        anion_positions[time, :, :] = anions.positions - COM
        cation_positions[time, :, :] = cations.positions - COM
        #cation_positions[time, :, :] = cations.center_of_geometry(compound = 'residues') - COM
        time += 1
    return anion_positions, cation_positions

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def calculateLii_self(ion_positions, timeSteps):
    """ 
    Function to calculate the "MSD" for the self component for a diagonal transport coefficient (L^{ii}).

    --------------------------
    Parameters
    --------------------------
    ion_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each ion as it varies over time.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively.
    timeSteps: float for the number of time steps at which the positions were recoarded in the simulation

    --------------------------
    Returns
    --------------------------
    msd: float array which corresponds to the "MSD" corresponding to the L^{ii}_{self} transport coefficient at each time step
    """
    Lii_self = np.zeros(timeSteps)
    for i in range(np.shape(ion_positions)[1]):
        Lii_self += getMSD(ion_positions[:, i, :])
    return Lii_self

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def calculateLii(ion_positions, timeSteps):
    """ 
    Function to calculate the "MSD" for the diagonal transport coefficient L^{ii}. 

    --------------------------
    Parameters
    --------------------------
    ion_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each ion as it varies over time.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively.
    timeSteps: float for the number of time steps at which the positions were recoarded in the simulation

    --------------------------
    Returns
    --------------------------
    msd: float array which corresponds to the "MSD" corresponding to the L^{ii} transport coefficient at each time step
    """
    r_sum = np.sum(ion_positions, axis = 1)
    return getMSD(r_sum)

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def calculateLij(cation_positions, anion_positions, timeSteps):
    """
    Function to calculate the "MSD" for the off-diagonal transport coefficient L^{ij}, i \neq j.

    ---------------------------
    Parameters
    ---------------------------
    cation_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each cation as it varies over time.
    anion_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each anion as it varies over time.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively.
    timeSteps: float for the number of time steps at which the positions were recoarded in the simulation

    --------------------------
    Returns
    --------------------------
    msd: float array which corresponds to the "MSD" corresponding to the L^{ij} transport coefficient at each time step
    """
    r_cat = np.sum(cation_positions, axis = 1)
    r_an = np.sum(anion_positions, axis = 1)
    return getMSDcross(r_cat, r_an)

@nb.jit(nopython=True)
def calculateLijs(cation_positions, anion_positions, timeSteps):
    """
    Function to calculate the "MSDs" for all transport coefficients.

    ---------------------------
    Parameters
    ---------------------------
    cation_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each cation as it varies over time.
    anion_positions: three dimensional float array containing the coordinates of each anion as it varies over time.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively.
    timeSteps: float for the number of time steps at which the positions were recoarded in the simulation
    volume : float storing the volume of the simulation box in \AA^3

    --------------------------
    Returns
    --------------------------
    msds: a list of float arraya containing the "MSDs" corresponding to each transport coefficient,
    L^{++}, L^{++}_{self}, L^{--}, L^{--}_{self}, L^{+-}
    """
    msd = np.zeros((timeSteps, 5))
    msd[:, 0] = calculateLii_self(cation_positions, timeSteps)
    msd[:, 1] =  calculateLii_self(anion_positions, timeSteps)
    msd[:, 2] = calculateLii(cation_positions, timeSteps)
    msd[:, 3] = calculateLii(anion_positions, timeSteps)
    msd[:, 4] = calculateLij(cation_positions, anion_positions, timeSteps)
    return msd

def fit_data(y, start, end, x):
    """
    Perform a linear regression.
    :param f: array[float], "MSD" data
    :param start: int, time index at which to start fitting
    :param end: int, time index at which to end fitting
    :param times: array[float], times at which position data was collected in the simulation
    :return lij: float, transport coefficient, i.e., slope of "MSD" in fitting region
    """
    params, r_value = np.linalg.lstsq(np.vstack([x, np.ones(len(x))]).T, y, rcond=None)[:2]
    return params[0]

def calculateCoefficients(noOfRuns, timeSteps):
    msds = np.zeros((timeSteps, 5, noOfRuns))
    for i in range(noOfRuns):
        topo_file = "../Downloads/nvt_il2/nvt.gro"  # LAMMPS data file contatining atom coordinates and topology
        traj_file = f"../Downloads/nvt_il2/nvt_calc{i}.xtc" # trajectory files
        sim = mda.Universe(topo_file, traj_file)
        anions = sim.select_atoms('resname NTf2 and name N5')
        cations = sim.select_atoms('resname LIG and name N01')

        anion_positions, cation_positions = getPositions(sim, anions, cations, timeSteps)
        msds[:, :, i] = calculateLijs(cation_positions, anion_positions, timeSteps)# / (6 * sim.dimensions[0]**3.0 * scipy.constants.k * 400)
    return msds

def getPositions_(u, anions, cations, timeSteps):
    """
    Creates an array containing the positions of all cations and anions over time.

    -------------------------
    Inputs:
    -------------------------
    u         : an MDAnalysis universe
    anions    : an MDAnalysis AtomGroup containing the centre of mass of the anions
    cations   : an MDAnalysis AtomGroup containing the centre of mass of the cations
    timeSteps : int, number of time steps at which the position of the atoms was recorded

    -------------------------
    Returns:
    -------------------------
    anion_positions  : float array with all anion centre of geometry positions.
    cation_positions : float array with all cation centre of geometry positions.
    Indices correspond to time, ion index, and spatial dimension (x,y,z), respectively
    """
    time = 0
    anion_positions = np.zeros((timeSteps, len(anions), 3), dtype = np.float32)
    cation_positions = np.zeros((timeSteps, len(cations), 3), dtype = np.float32)
    COM = u.atoms.center_of_mass(wrap = True)
    for ts in u.trajectory:
        anion_positions[time, :, :] = anions.positions - COM
        cation_positions[time, :, :] = cations.positions - COM
        #cation_positions[time, :, :] = cations.center_of_geometry(compound = 'residues') - COM
        time += 1
    return anion_positions, cation_positions

def calculateCoefficients_(noOfRuns, timeSteps):

    for i in range(noOfRuns):
